io.foxtrot.common.core.models.route

Class Route

  • Object
    • io.foxtrot.common.core.models.route.Route

  • public final class Route
extends Object
    Describes your route. This object is used to import new routes into Foxtrot. Once a route has been imported, a new OptimizedRoute object will be returned to you via your registered RouteStateListener with the optimized route.

    Fields:

    Name Type Required? Description
    startTime DateTime true The start time of the route
    name String true The name of the route. This field cannot have more than 200 characters.
    warehouse Warehouse true DEPRECATED: Please use startingWarehouse and endingWarehouse. The same warehouse can be specified in both. The method will be removed soon \n The warehouse information. This is the beginning and ending point of your route
    startingWarehouse Warehouse true The starting warehouse information. This is the starting point of your route
    endingWarehouse Warehouse true The ending warehouse information. This is the ending point of your route
    waypoints Collection<Waypoint> true Collection of Waypoint objects. This collection must not be empty.
    vehicle Vehicle false Vehicle associated with this route 

    
   Collection<Waypoint> waypoints = ...
   Warehouse startingWarehouse = ...
   Warehouse endingWarehouse = ...
   Route route = Route.builder()
                      .setName("Route A")
                      .setStartTime(new DateTime(1467053939000, DateTimeZone.UTC))
                      .setWaypoints(waypoints)
                      .setStartingWarehouse(startingWarehouse)
                      .setEndingWarehouse(endingWarehouse)
                      .setVehicle(Vehicle.builder()
                                         .setPlateNumber("ABC-1234")
                                         .build())
                      .build();
    See Also:
    Route.Builder
